on of Gods: Similar to ancient polytheistic traditions, the Church's gods represent aspects of life and death, guiding the Reclaimers to restore order.\n  \n5. Environmental and Historical Context\n- Pre-Calamity: Highly organized civilizations with city-states, infrastructure, and magic. The calamity shattered this civilization, leaving the world in ruins.\n- Post-Calamity: A world filled with dangers, where survivors cling to fortified enclaves, and the Reclaimers fight to restore balance.\n\n6. Potential Connection to Abrahamic Religions\n- Theological Shift: Over time, the Church’s polytheism could evolve into monotheism, setting the stage for early Abrahamic religions.\n- Historical Setting: The story may take place between the Younger and Older Dryas periods, echoing the environmental turmoil of prehistory.\n"
