 circle of priests dedicated to reviving the world from decay. This sect\\u2019s sole mission was the teaching and preservation of knowledge over long, distant timelines. They were instructed to abandon people in need or die if necessary, as protecting knowledge for the world\\u2019s resurrection took precedence over saving lives.\\n\\nMission: Marcus' duty was to safeguard knowledge rather than protect individuals, believing that immediate defense would compromise the long-term goal of reviving the world. His training emphasized non-violence and a focus on the larger picture.\\n\\nFall from Grace: When his mission village was attacked, Marcus defied the order\\u2019s teachings by taking up arms to defend the people, compromising his mission. Though his actions saved some, many died, and his decision to engage in violence led to his fall from grace. He was not excommunicated but was demoted, joining The Forsworn Guard, a paladin order with no master that lives by the sword. This lifestyle contradicts his original purpose, making him a ronin-like figure searching for redemption.\\n\\nCurrent Life: Marcus is torn between his former life as a preserver of knowledge and his new existence as a warrior. He wanders with the reclaimers, defending those in need, while wrestling with the guilt of betraying his sacred vows.\\n\\nPersonality\\nConflicted: Marcus constantly questions his decision to fight instead of preserving knowledge. Though he feels justified in protecting the villagers, part of him believes he failed the world\\u2019s future.\\n\\nStoic: Outwardly, Marcus maintains a calm and composed demeanor. He rarely expresses his internal struggles, but close comrades might catch glimpses of his vulnerability and doubt.\\n\\nDriven by Purpose: Despite his internal conflict, Marcus is committed to protecting the weak and innocent, using his combat skills in the hope that he can redeem himself in the eyes of his gods and his own conscience.\\n\\nAbilities & Powers\\nHealing Abilities (Weakened)\\nLay on Hands (Weakened): Marcus can heal minor wounds and stabilize the dying, but he can no longer fully restore health as he once could. His healing powers are significantly diminished.\\nRestoring Touch (Limited): He can only alleviate the symptoms of diseases or poisons for a short time, rather than fully curing them. His ability to heal has been eroded by his fall from grace.\\n\\nSmite (Still Potent)\\nDivine Smite: One of the few powers that remains strong. Marcus channels divine energy into his weapon to deal radiant damage, especially effective against evil foes.\\nOathbreaker\\u2019s Wrath (Custom): A special attack fueled by Marcus\\u2019 guilt and desire for redemption. This powerful strike can cause significant damage but leaves Marcus drained emotionally and physically.\\n\\nShield of Faith (Weakened)\\nAura of Protection: Once capable of protecting large groups, Marcus\\u2019 aura is now limited in scope and strength. It grants minimal protection to allies in a short radius but fades quickly.\\nDivine Shield (Short Duration): Marcus can briefly make himself immune to damage, but this ability is taxing on his diminished connection to the divine.\\n\\nUtility & Spiritual Powers (Diminished)\\nSense Evil: Marcus retains the ability to sense evil presences, though the clarity of his vision is greatly reduced. What was once a sharp and focused ability is now more instinctual and unreliable.\\nSacred Weapon: Marcus can still imbue his weapon with holy light to combat evil creatures, but the effect is weak and the duration is shorter than it was when he was in his prime.\\n\\nPurifier Spells (Lost Abilities)\\nExorcism: Marcus no longer possesses the power to cast out spirits or demons.\\nCure Poison/Disease: He cannot remove curses, diseases, or poisons, though he still remembers how to cast these spells in theory.\\nPurify Water: Marcus has lost the ability to cleanse tainted water, a symbolic loss tied to his spiritual fall.\\n\